This proposal supports the Colville Indian Tribe in this HCAX project through the EPA- Exchange Network FY 2020. It will inform environmental decisions and reporting requirements related to both ESA-listed and non-listed salmon and steelhead, as well as species that rely on these fish as prey resources, such as Southern Resident Orca whales (2019 recommendations: 
 https://www.governor.wa.gov/sites/default/files/OrcaTaskForce_FinalReportandRecommendations_11.07.19.pdf ). This grant will enable fisheries biologists of the WDFW, Colville Tribes, StreamNet and PNAMP staff, including biologists from Idaho Department of Fish and Game (IDFG) and Oregon Department of Fisheries and Wildlife (ODFW), to achieve the following major outputs or outcomes in collaboration with their data management, developer, and programmer experts: 
 Â· advance sharing of standardized metrics and HLIs for hatchery salmon and steelhead in a well-defined, transparent manner across the Pacific Northwest within EPAs Region 10;
 Â· improve consistency in the information communicated with the public, and used for environmental reporting required by and for regional decision-making in multiple forums;
 Â· support and contribute to the reporting for states, tribes, tribal consortia, federal agencies (BPA, US Fish and Wildlife Service, and National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA)-Fisheries) and other partners: NPCC, Oregon Watershed Enhancement Board, and G SRO (see Table 2, Attachment- Formal Partners).
